--- title: "test.csv" author: "Choo Jian Yuan" output: bookdown::html_document2 editor: visual --- **Date:** 12/06/2025 #### Before use the data for my analysis, preemptive checking has been done and result as per below： ```{=html} ``` ::: {#summaryPanel .table-of-summary} Summary of checking - `passenger_id` column has data length of 3 to 4 digits character. Result show in section - Direct - `sex` column has only 2 unique value which are female and male. Result show in section - Direct - `ticket` column shows 60 duplicates. I found out dupplication is due to family members might share the same ticket. Result show in section - Direct - `cabin` column shows 327 row with NA. However, this will not cause any issue as cabin is not within part of our assessment. Result show in section - Direct - `embarked` column shows 3 unique values of C , Q and S. Result show in section - Direct - `pclass`column seperated all tickets into 3 classes of 1 , 2 and 3. Result show in section - Direct - `age` column represents passengers' age when boarded titanic. Result show in section - Direct - `sib_sp` column represents the total number of siblings and spouses who boarded the ship along with each passenger. Result show in section - Direct - `parch` column represents the total number of parents and children who boarded the ship along with each passenger. Result show in section - Direct - `fare` column represents ticket fee for onboarding. Max, Min, Median and Mean have been calculated. Result show in section - Direct - Full dataset Direct ::: ```{=html} ```

Summary for Embarkation

::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} #C - embarked from Cherbourg #Q - embarked from Queenstown #S - embarked from Southampton. Embarkation_category <- sort(unique(data2$embarked)) Embarkation_detail <- function(Xs){ results <- c() for(x in Xs){ #Detail clarification adjustment_x <- if(x == "C"){"Cherbourg"} else if(x == "Q"){"Queenstown"} else if(x == "S"){"Southampton"} else {as.character(x)} count <- sum(data2[,"embarked"]==x) sample_samples <- if(count>1){" samples are "}else{" sample is "} result <- paste0(count, sample_samples, "found with embarked = ", adjustment_x) results <- c(results, result) } return(results) } Embarkation_detail(Embarkation_category) %>% result_display(.,"Below refer to onboarding location") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
Below refer to onboarding location
Output :
102 samples are found with embarked = Cherbourg
46 samples are found with embarked = Queenstown
270 samples are found with embarked = Southampton
````` ::: :::

Summary for Pclass

::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} # 1 - 1st class # 2 - 2nd class # 3 - 3rd class pclass_category <- sort(unique(data2$pclass)) pclass_detail <- function(Xs){ results <- c() for(x in Xs){ #Detail clarification adjustment_x <- if( x == 1 ){"1st class"} else if( x == 2 ){"2nd class"} else if( x == 3 ){"3rd class"} else {as.character(x)} count <- sum(data2[,"pclass"] == x) sample_samples <- if(count>1){" samples are"}else{" sample is"} result <- paste0(count, sample_samples, " found with pclass = ", adjustment_x) results <- c(results, result) } return(results) } pclass_detail(pclass_category) %>% result_display(.,"") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}

````` ::: :::
